      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING SPIRIT (1) missed a nose here in Open grade when heavily bet off back-to-back wins at the track. Then tackled a tougher Open at the Sunshine Coast, where he didn't finish it off. Gets in well with a 3kg claim in easier company and he can add to his impressive record at the track. UNIVERSAL HARMONY (5) is a leader who has a super record this course and distance. Was last seen winning a CL6 easily over 1200m at Mackay and he flies fresh. May control the race from an inside gate and 3x winning rider McIver is reunited. ELECTRIC BRAE (9) sits way down in the weights and has pieces of form that would see her very competitive. Has some gear switches for this. PRETTY SLICK (8) found won better this track/trip in a 64 and had raced in Open grade prior. Carries 4kg less with Stewart up, and has to be considered as well.",
